<span id="v.iv.ix.xxxi"></span>

<span id="v.iv.ix.xxxi-p1"></span> <span class="c11"><span
id="v.iv.ix.xxxi-p1.1"></span>Chapter 31.—</span>60.  Tenax of Horrea
Celiæ <span id="fr_1841"></span>[1842](#fn_1841.md) said:  "There is one
baptism, but of the Church; and where the Church is not, there baptism
also cannot be." <span id="fr_1842"></span>[1843](#fn_1842.md)

<span id="v.iv.ix.xxxi-p4"></span>61.  To him we answer:  How then comes
it that it may be where the rock is not, but only sand; seeing that the
Church is on the rock, and not on sand?

